The distinction between mental determination and mental action remains open for the Bhāṣya pass.

## 12. Commit Note

Committed VAK_4d / VAkK_4.64.

Established:
- the threefold silence of perfected body, speech, and mind
- threefold purity as the complete threefold good conduct
- silence as purified activity rather than inactivity
- the textual asymmetry between bodily/verbal karma and mind
- the transition toward duścarita and the ten karmapathas

First-pass determination:

```text
mauna-traya
    = perfected body, speech, and mind

śauca-traya
    = complete bodily, verbal, and mental good conduct

silence
    ≠ inactivity

silence
    = purified activity beyond further training
```
